<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1042" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1042">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/1404a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                all <gloss type="to">Seaport Consuls</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-11">
                                <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Circular telegram]</p>
                        <p>You need not report further in response to circular instructions of
                            November 22<note n="6" xml:id="d1042fn6">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, p.<ref target="#pg_634">634</ref>
                            </note> and following relative to unneutral service, except in
                            suspicious cases. You will not, however, relax your vigilance to obtain
                            and report information regarding violations of American neutrality and
                            transshipment of cargoes at sea to belligerent warships.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>